solution:
Note that $S$ is the upper-half of a sphere with radius 5.

Let $s$ be the side length of the cube.  Then one face of the cube aligns with the $xy$-plane; the center of this face is at $O = (0,0,0).$

[asy]
unitsize(1.2 cm);

pair A, B, C, D, O, T, X, Y, Z;
pair x, y, z;

x = (2,-0.2);
y = (1.2,0.8);
z = (0,2);

X = (0,0);
Y = x;
T = y;
A = z;
Z = x + y;
B = x + z;
D = y + z;
C = x + y + z;
O = (X + Y + T + Z)/4;

draw(X--Y--Z--C--D--A--cycle);
draw(B--A);
draw(B--C);
draw(B--Y);
draw(T--X,dashed);
draw(T--D,dashed);
draw(T--Z,dashed);
draw(O--Z,dashed);
draw(O--C,dashed);

label("$A$", Z, E);
label("$B$", C, NE);
dot("$O$", O, SW);
label("$s$", (C + Z)/2, dir(0));
[/asy]

